        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:58PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ethelsville, or near Columbus, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ethelsville, North Pickens Airport, Millport, McShan, Gordo, Shaw,
Owens, Lubbub, Forest, Macedonia, Reform, Melborne, Ashcraft Corner,
and Kennedy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Alabama.</instruction>
